Smart Traffic Light Controller — Phase 2 Algorithm
CS 240 | Dr. Dube | Cuesta College | Group: Rhooti
1. Start program.

2. Initialize system.
  - Set all lights to RED.
  - Clear all flags.

3. Repeat forever:
  - Continuously check for keyboard input throughout each phase.
  - If emergency key is pressed, go to Step 5 immediately.
  - If pedestrian key is pressed, set pedestrian flag and continue.
  - Run North-South green phase — hold for full green duration.
  - Run North-South yellow phase — hold for yellow duration.
  - Transition to ALL RED.
  - If pedestrian flag is set, extend hold for crossing, then clear flag.
  - Run East-West green phase — hold for full green duration.
  - Run East-West yellow phase — hold for yellow duration.
  - Transition to ALL RED.
  - If pedestrian flag is set, extend hold for crossing, then clear flag.
  - Return to top of loop.

4. Pedestrian procedure:
  - Hold all lights RED for extended crossing duration.
  - Clear pedestrian flag.
  - Return.

5. Emergency procedure:
  - Force all lights to RED immediately.
  - Hold for emergency duration to allow vehicle to pass.
  - Return to top of main loop.
